title: no kokoro-onnx version 0.3.9 found by pip
body:
The below error is popping when running pip install -r requirements.txt
I cant seem to find a version 0.3.9. Is this issue on my end or due to some update?

"ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement kokoro-onnx==0.3.9 (from versions: 0.1.0, 0.1.1, 0.1.2, 0.1.3, 0.1.4, 0.1.5, 0.1.6, 0.1.7, 0.1.8, 0.1.9, 0.2.0, 0.2.1, 0.2.2, 0.2.3, 0.4.4, 0.4.5)
ERROR: No matching distribution found for kokoro-onnx==0.3.9"
author: CrimsonWillow

comments.body:
can't reproduce,

you must have supported python environment
>requires-python = ">=3.9, <3.13"
Ah, don't know how I missed this. Issue solved. Thanks

satisfaction_conditions: Explanation of why the package version cannot be found
Information about environment requirements for the package
